<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Three <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">architrave</rs> blocks, complete or in fragments, with architrave and <rs type="decoration">frieze</rs> cut in one on both faces; lettered from left to right: a two fragments, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.58</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.647</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.60</measure>; b <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">3.20</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.66</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.66</measure>; c two joining fragments (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.05</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.66</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.41</measure>). On one face, the frieze area is decorated with <rs type="decoration">faces</rs> and <rs type="decoration">masks</rs> in relief, but no inscription.</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p> The opposite side has no decoration, but the first line of the inscription is cut in the area of the frieze; the second line is cut on the uppermost of the three fasciae of the architrave. On block B a further text was cut, probably in the fourth century, on the lower two fasciae, and subsequently efficiently erased.</p>
</div>
